<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-11-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1950-12-31T11:00:00-05:00" n="801" subtype="editorial-note" type="document" xml:id="d801">
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                            </head>
                            <p>On December 21, 1951, the Department sent to all diplomatic, <gloss target="#t_TCA1">TCA</gloss>, and <gloss target="#t_ECA1">ECA</gloss> missions in the Far East and South Asia a circular
                                airgram on the subject “Relationship With Japan and Production of
                                Essential Materials.” For text, see <ref target="#pg_126">page
                                    126</ref>.</p>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>